definition: set up on high (idiom); not in touch with reality/aloof and remote
(located) at/(to be) in/to exist/in the middle of doing sth/(indicating an action in progress)
on top/upon/above/upper/previous/first (of multiple parts)/to climb/to get onto/to go up/to attend (class or university)

sentences.english: The goblin was trembling, unable to meet the red eyes high above his.
sentences.chinese: 那個妖精在發抖，不敢正視高高在上的那雙紅眼睛。

sentences.english: She is a very poor singer but she thinks she's the bee's knees.
sentences.chinese: 她五音不全卻自認爲是高高在上的一流歌手。

sentences.english: Saint Valentine thou who art crowned aloft.
sentences.chinese: 聖瓦倫丁河啊，你戴着王冠高高在上。

sentences.english: Women want men that appear high on the social ladder.
sentences.chinese: 女人想要在社會階梯中顯得高高在上的男人。

sentences.english: He, high above, I feel only to sediment.
sentences.chinese: 他，高高在上，我感覺自己只不過是地底泥。

sentences.english: I do know sugar will be much higher in years to come.
sentences.chinese: 但我能確定糖價在未來數年將高高在上。

sentences.english: I try not to dictate it, not to play God.
sentences.chinese: 我試着不去指揮它，不扮演高高在上的神的角色。

sentences.english: The sky, the world above, is really bound up with the world below.
sentences.chinese: 高高在上的天空與，下面的世界確實密不可分。

sentences.english: America's reputation is in the toilet, while China's is on the rise.
sentences.chinese: 美國的聲譽在糞坑裏，而中國則高高在上。

sentences.english: Mr. Whitford stands aloof from any notice of small fry.
sentences.chinese: 惠特福德先生高高在上，從來不注意小人物。

sentences.english: Don't act so all-fired high and mighty.
sentences.chinese: 不要表現出一副高高在上的樣子。

sentences.english: That two-eyed monster God is still above.
sentences.chinese: 那兩隻眼的大怪上帝依然高高在上。

sentences.english: You are so used to being on top, but you will drop to second place.
sentences.chinese: 你們一直習慣於高高在上，但是你們終究會退居次席。

sentences.english: His stare is one of regal aloofness.
sentences.chinese: 他看人的眼神還是那種高高在上的神態。

definition: too high to reach (idiom); eminent and unapproachable
lit. to order people by pointing the chin (idiom); to signal orders by facial gesture/arrogant and bossy
the eye can see nothing worthwhile all around (idiom); arrogant/condescending/supercilious
to bow and bend the knee (idiom); fawning/bending and scraping to curry favor
to consider oneself unexcelled in the world/to be insufferably arrogant
to tilt one's head back to see (sth)/to look up at
to be on an equal footing
to think highly of oneself (idiom); giving oneself airs/arrogant and self-important
